.\" _printf man page /usr/share/man/man3/printf
.\"
.PRINTF 3 "24-10-2021" "ALX-printf"

.SH NAME
_printf

.B_printf - format and print data. Part of a project at ALX.

.SH SYNOPSIS
This project aims to mimic the printf found in C programming.

_printf FORMAT [ARGUMENT]...
.ss

.SH DESCRIPTION

_printf() the function produces output according to format string that \
specifies how subsequent arguments are written and converted to stdout, the \
standard output stream.

_printf() loops through the format for a conversion specifier (%). If one is found\
, it will then access an array of structures and match the corresponding character \
with the corresponding function. The specified function will return a string-converted \
version of the result and immediately passed into the buffer.

.SH CONVERSION SPECIFIERS

.IP %c
prints out a character.

.IP %d
prints an integer, similar to %i.

.IP %s
prints a string.

.IP %u
Prints unsigned int.

.IP %o
Converts unsigned int to octal.

.IP %x
Converts unsigned int to hexadecimal (lowercase)

.IP %X
Converts unsigned int to hexadecimal (uppercase)

.IP %r
Prints reverse of intput string

.IP %R
Converts string to rot13

.SH OPTIONS

Pending

.SH FORMAT
controls the output as in C printf.  Interpreted sequences are:

       \n     new line

       \t     tab

       %%     a single %

.SS Example
.RS
_printf("Duck %s", "Sauce");
Prints string "Duck Sauce"

.RE

.SS Return Value
Upon success, these main function will return the number of characters printed.

.SH "SEE ALSO"
.SH ""

.BR printf(1)

.P

.SH BUGS
Memory issues.

